03, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice de Bromehall was born as the daughter of Geoffrey de Bromhall and Margery Wettenhall. She had at least 1 son with John Davenport."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1340–1403":"1340–1403","–Female":"Surnud","1281–Male":"1281–Surnud","1365–1436":"1365–1436","1310–1375":"1310–1375","1436":"1436","1403":"1403","1334":"1334","1365":"1365","1310":"1310","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1281":"1281","Bramall Hall, Bramhall, Wrenbury, Cheshire, England":"Bramhall, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stockport, Greater Manchester, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Stockport, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1340–1403":"1340–1403","–Female":"Kuollut","1281–Male":"1281–Kuollut","1365–1436":"1365–1436","1310–1375":"1310–1375","1436":"1436","1403":"1403","1334":"1334","1365":"1365","1310":"1310","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1281":"1281","Bramall Hall, Bramhall, Wrenbury, Cheshire, England":"Bramhall, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stockport, Greater Manchester, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Stockport, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1340–1403":"1340–1403","–Female":"Décédée","1281–Male":"1281–Décédé","1365–1436":"1365–1436","1310–1375":"1310–1375","1436":"1436","1403":"1403","1334":"1334","1365":"1365","